<br>
-Ability to run normal chants (speed, dmg, heal) with one resist chant concurrently<br>
<br>
-Endurance tap. This hasn't been introduced into the game as of yet. I think the Skald is a great candidate for it. Put it on a 30 second timer, let it fill %25 of your end bar at the highest level. Either convert one of the DDs to the end tap or make it a seperate spell that does endurance damage only to the target. Endurance is a big problem for skalds (especially non-hammer users) without a shammy in the group due to high style costs and shouts using up end. This might help alieviate some of that.<br>
<br>
-Give skalds the ability to debuff melee resists. Magic debuffs are present everywhere in daoc. Melee debuffs are not. I think Skalds are a great candidate for this. Nothing too overpowering, but maybe a shout that cuts their slash resist by 5-10%. This shouldn't be an interrupting shout. If we are meant to be in the thick of things and lack the survivability of real tanks and even other hybrids, we should be given a few more tools to allow us to be more effective in battle. Hell, a champ can run up to a target, debuff them to almost nothing and two shot them with annhiliation. I think this change wouldn't even be on that level.<br>
<br>
-Along the same lines, possibly an AF debuff would be an alternative if the melee resists are not feasible.<br>
<br>
-Personal mez reduction chant. Midgard is by far the easiest realm to land good crowd control on. No defense from RAs (SoS, Group Purge), no mez reduction. Having skalds breaking mez a little sooner might give them some additional utility.<br>
<br>
-A 99% root shout, but with 150 Range. 1 min timer, 30 second duration So, not really overpowering in terms of an interrupt, but very useful in negating a tank from a battle for 30 seconds or so. You would have to be within weapon range to use it, so I can't see this being a huge issue.<br>
<br>
-For a Skald unique RA, give them a group melee boost of about 25% greater dps for 1 min duration on a 30 minute timer. Powerful? Yes. I would still rather have Faith Heal/Group Purge/Speed of Sound/Bunker of Faith/Brilliant Aura of Deflection/Thornweed Field/Ichor of the Deep<br>
<br>
So, add in your own brainstormin ideas, critique these however harshly. Just thinking that now that it is obvious that the devs can see that skalds have some issues we can make some strides to make skalds into a class to be feared again (as opposed to laughed at).<br>
<br>
